jei.mowlib.item.applicator.description: §3 Crouch Right Click to Save Color, Right Click to Apply Color, Offhand and Any Placed Colorable blocks will be placed with the currently selected color.
jei.mowlib.item.repair_note.description: §3 Right Click on a Machine or Workstation that is 'smoking' to receive a new repair request. If it is enchanted, right clicking again will just get another repair request unless the first request hasn't been fulfilled.
jei.mowlib.tag_getter.description: §5 This Gets Tags off Items and Blocks for use when setting up the Tag Filter
jei.mowlib.tag_getter.interaction: §3 For Blocks: Offhand Item and Crouch Right Click to get Tags from a block in-world.(Clicking in the air will instead cycle the selected tag) For Items: Offhand the item and with this in your main hand, right click.(No item in offhand will cycle the selected tag) While the item in in you main hand, crouch right click to clear all tags.
jei.mowlib.tool_dev.description: §5 Somewhat Useful Tool for creative mode users
jei.mowlib.tool_dev.interaction: §5 Offhand item with NBT and right click tool (in air) to display the NBT string in chat. Offhand Honey Comb and right click tool on Hive Block to 'fill' it.
jei.mowlib.tool_filter.interaction: §5 Crouch Right Click in Air to Swap to a Different Tool, Remove Filters by Offhanding Tool and Left Clicking Block
jei.mowlib.tool_tag.description: §5 Used to Make Tag related Items, and make Tags off of items/blocks viewable in game
jei.mowlib.tool_tag.interaction: §5 Crouch Right Click in Air to Swap to a Different Tool, Offhand Item/Block and Right Click Tool, Will Display the Tags on the Item/Block in the Players Chat.
jei.mowlib.tool_work.interaction: §5 Crouch Right Click in Air to Swap to a Different Tool, Remove Work Cards by Offhanding Tool and Left Clicking Block
jei.mowlib.workcard_area.description: §5Right Click two blocks to define the Work Area corresponding to all locations contained between those points. Right Click in the air to clear all existing selections.
jei.mowlib.workcard_belocations.descript: §5Right Click a block containing a 'MowLib' block entity (like a Pedestal) to add it to the defined Work Area if not already present, or to remove it from the defined Work Area if it was already present. Right Click in the air to clear all existing selections.
jei.mowlib.workcard_locations.descriptio: §5Right Click a block to add it to the defined Work Area if not already present, or to remove it from the defined Work Area if it was already present. Right Click in the air to clear all existing selections.
